---
import AdBanner from '../../components/banner/AdBanner';
import ToolContainer from '../../components/tool/ToolContainer';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  name="MCP Directory Credits"
  path="/freedevtools/mcp/credits"
  title="MCP Directory Credits & Acknowledgments | Online Free DevTools by Hexmos"
  description="Credits and acknowledgments for the MCP (Model Context Protocol) repositories available on Free DevTools. Learn about the sources, contributors, and data sources."
  canonical="https://hexmos.com/freedevtools/mcp/credits/"
  themeColor="#3b82f6"
  showSidebar={false}
  showHeader={true}
>
 <ToolContainer>
    <div class="mb-16 mt-[74px]">
      <AdBanner client:visible />
    </div>
    
    <div class="mb-8">
      <nav class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-4">
        <a href="/freedevtools/" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Free DevTools</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <a href="/freedevtools/mcp/1/" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">MCP Directory</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span>Credits</span>
      </nav>
      
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">
        MCP Directory Credits & Acknowledgments
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6">
        We thank the creators, contributors, and maintainers who have made the MCP ecosystem possible.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>Data Sources</h2>
      <p>
        The MCP repository data available on Free DevTools is sourced from several excellent community-maintained resources:
      </p>
      
      <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Primary Data Sources</h3>
        
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
              <a href="https://github.com/metorial/mcp-index" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">
                MCP Index by Metorial
              </a>
            </h4>
            <p class="text-sm">Comprehensive index of MCP servers with detailed metadata, categories, and descriptions.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
              <a href="https://github.com/punkpeye/awesome-mcp-servers" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">
                Awesome MCP Servers by Punkpeye
              </a>
            </h4>
            <p class="text-sm">Curated list of awesome MCP servers with community recommendations and use cases.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
              <a href="https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">
                Official MCP Servers Repository
              </a>
            </h4>
            <p class="text-sm">Official repository maintained by the Model Context Protocol team with reference implementations.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>What is MCP?</h2>
      <p>
        The Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open standard that enables AI assistants to securely connect to data sources and tools. 
        It allows AI models to access real-time information, perform actions, and interact with external systems in a controlled and secure manner.
      </p>

      <h2>Repository Information</h2>
      <p>
        Each MCP repository listed includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Repository Details</strong> - Name, description, author, and license information</li>
        <li><strong>Statistics</strong> - GitHub stars, weekly downloads, and tool counts</li>
        <li><strong>Categories</strong> - Organized by functionality and use case</li>
        <li><strong>Documentation</strong> - README content and usage examples</li>
        <li><strong>Links</strong> - Direct access to GitHub and NPM pages</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data Processing</h2>
      <p>
        Our data processing pipeline:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Aggregates data from multiple community sources</li>
        <li>Normalizes repository information and metadata</li>
        <li>Categorizes servers by functionality and use case</li>
        <li>Fetches real-time statistics from GitHub and NPM APIs</li>
        <li>Processes README content for better searchability</li>
        <li>Updates information regularly to ensure accuracy</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Contributing</h2>
      <p>
        If you have suggestions for improving the MCP Directory or want to report issues:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Submit issues or pull requests to our GitHub repository</li>
        <li>Suggest new MCP servers that should be included</li>
        <li>Help improve categorization and metadata</li>
        <li>Contribute to the upstream data sources we rely on</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>License Information</h2>
      <p>
        The MCP Directory itself is open source and available under the MIT License. 
        Individual MCP servers maintain their own licenses, which are displayed on their respective pages.
      </p>

      <h2>Special Thanks</h2>
      <p>
        We extend our gratitude to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>MCP Community</strong> - For building and maintaining an amazing ecosystem of tools</li>
        <li><strong>Data Source Maintainers</strong> - For their tireless work curating and updating repository information</li>
        <li><strong>MCP Protocol Team</strong> - For creating and maintaining the Model Context Protocol standard</li>
        <li><strong>Repository Authors</strong> - For sharing their innovative MCP servers with the community</li>
        <li><strong>Contributors</strong> - Everyone who has helped improve the MCP ecosystem</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about the MCP Directory, want to report an issue, or have suggestions for improvement, 
        please contact us through our main website or GitHub repository.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Back Navigation -->
    <div class="mt-10 pt-6 mb-8 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a 
          href="/freedevtools/mcp/1/" 
          class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-100 dark:hover:bg-blue-900/30 transition-colors"
        >
          ‚Üê  Back to MCP Directory
        </a>
        <a 
          href="/freedevtools/" 
          class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-lg hover:bg-slate-100 dark:hover:bg-slate-700 transition-colors"
        >
          Free DevTools Home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </ToolContainer>
</BaseLayout>
